caption: "Perhaps the top fish restaurant in the entire USA."  I wrote this about a year ago.  My wife and I had been planning on coming back next time we were in D.C.  Then we got news that the owner/ Chef had died in early 2021.  Very sad news.  He was charming. After he had cooked us amazing plate after plate of different fishes, he came out and we sat and drank together until around 2 in the morning.  It was so special we had been trying to plan for another trip from New York with our main purpose being to have another night like that, then Covid hit.  Our sympathy for the staff which were like family to him, and his family and children for their loss.
Staff is very attentive and so nice!
This place constantly delivers. They serve good dishes for fair prices, there is no waiting time even when the spot is loaded.
Fantastic. Everything was delicious and perfectly cooked. You really can't go wrong!
Fantastic restaurant!

My favorite restaurant.  Food is consistently not just good, but mind bogglingly amazing, staff are great, wine selection and cocktails top notch, and it's been that way since my first visit 13 years ago.  I've looked forward to every chance to visit as I've moved around the country and so excited to be back in the DMV and able to stop by more often!

At the moment  you step in that restaurant  team give you a good feeling. Very hospitable hosts, it is a nice place to  enjoy with friends or with your date. delightful  cooking, specialist  chef, modest  price and excellent  service. Highly recommended.
Tried this spot in the past with my friend and I am obsessed since then. I love the great character and tasty dishes and beverages. I recommend this place.

Restaurant has the potential to be something decent but poor staffing choices and lack-luster cuisine make that impossible here. Food was OK, but had expected better going in. Service was a tragically comical with one waitress comping atleast the first course for each of the 3 tables next to us due to delays/mistakes. (Our waiter was better but did not seem to care about the guest experience) Bar Tender came out screaming and cursing the kitchen at one point which silenced the whole restaurant and didn't end until another staff member intervened. Value was perhaps the biggest disappointment. The highlight we shared with the tables adjacent was the pure absurdity of the affair. It was an experience for sure, just not the one we'd expected!
Amazing fish entrees, unbelievable.

While the food was good the pricing was a bit vague , most of the options were appetizers and you are not given much time to choose , bill for one person added up to over 75$ they need to add some $$$ to this description .
Nice owner, great food
Fresh fish. Strongly recommend the Bronzini (grilled whole with herbs) with snap peas as side
Always great seafood, well prepared and presented. Staff helpful. Solid wine list.

Great neighborhood seafood spot. If you're not into fresh fish or shellfish, you may want to pass. Havent had anything that wasnt really good. Grilled octopus, calamari, and fresh walleye perfectly cooked.

Food was cooked to perfection and everything was fresh. We ordered the grilled octopus as an appetizer, and then the tuna and the lobster risotto (this was definitely the highlight) as the entrees. The flavors that each dish had worked amazing with each type of seafood/fish starring the dish, and the portions were perfect. We paired everything with a White Garnacha wine and it seemed to tie up everything together.  The location and ambiance of the restaurant were also very nice. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable of their dishes and wines.  If you like seafood, you will 100% enjoy this place.

Appetizers including octopus,tuna tartar and sardines were very good. Dinners including walleye, halibut and bronzini were very good. The lobster risotto dish was small, served cold, surprisingly sweet, bland and overpriced. The chocolate tart was amazing.
Great selection of very fresh fish and seafood prepared extremely well. A little more variety in vegetables and sides would have elevated an already exceptional meal.
Service was amazing and the food, twice that. Would recommend if you are visiting DC this place is Must
First time visit. Welcoming staff. A large menu. The food was fresh and delicious. Compared to other restaurants in the area, surprisingly quiet.  Will definitely return

Was recommended by a friend, and now every time I go to DC this is my new go to place. It's an absolutely amazing place. It is a tad expensive, but honestly, the quality of the food, service and atmosphere makes it almost a moot point. I seriously recommend this place.
A terrific upscale seafood joint.

Nice neighborhood eatery with good selections, though they could use a wine list refresh. We had the lobster special, and it was very good; bisque, a lobster and beet salad, followed by a full lobster, broken up in a lovely garlic and oil mix. It was busy but not too loud and the waiter was friendly and attentive.
Loved the grilled calamari and pesto pasta. will be back for some lobster
Overpriced for the quality/quantity of food served.

Totally enjoyed the Tuesday lobster special: cup of a savory lobster bisque, salad of lobster and red and golden beets, and 1+ pound lobster served on lemongrass melted butter. Only issue was the lobster shell was so hard that server had to take portions back to the chef to crack. I savored every bite. My companions enjoyed the beet and goat cheese salad, and 30+ mussels as appetizers, and the halibut with clams and branzino entrees. Although the complete bronzino was served as a display, it would have been pleasant for the server to deboned it as they always do in Italy. For dessert we enjoyed the sweet pie slice topped with slightly tart lingonberry sauce, goat cheesecake and raspberry sorbet.

So the food was really good here definitely 5 star taste but it was a bit expensive which would still earn it a 4.5 at least except end of the night during desert they poured us tap water and a full size probably 2 inch cockroach comes out of the pitcher into my moms glass.... so that was a bit gross. So 3 stars may be generous tbh

I recently had dinner at Pesce with my boss before a meeting in Washington. The restaurant was near Dupont Circle and between our hotels. We felt like seafood and gave it a try. We both had a drink, appetizer and an entree. While the food was ok. The value for what was served on the plate was another matter. If you have ever eaten at a restaurant and had to go eat afterwards then be prepared for that with Pesce.  I had the grilled octopus and my boss had the grilled calamari. The appetizers were ok but nothing that stood out. We were looking forward to the entree and both had the sea bass with vegetables and mushrooms. I would say that I was more surprised at the size of the entree it was a miniature portion for a 6 year old not an adult. My boss and I thought it was a joke and were looking around to see if we were being punked on camera. However, this was really happening. $32 for a piece of fish that wouldn't fill a kid. We ate and immediately left dissatisfied and upset at paying $ 80 each for what we were served. On my walk back to the Capital Hilton I found a poke restaurant called Aloha Poke near Dupont Circle, I got a small dish for $8 and was pleasantly surprised of the quality and freshness.  Note to Pesce, give your customers quality food and enough that doesn't make them feeling hungry after they leave.
Delicious food. Everything we tried was great. Will be back soon for Lobster Tuesday and desserts!

(Translated by Google) The food was delicious, not too expensive, and I felt that the cost performance was good. Correspondence of capacity was also polite and helpful !! Moth  (Original) 料理は美味しく、値段も高すぎず、コストパフォーマンスが良いと感じました。 定員さんの対応も丁寧で親切でした‼️
One of the best seafood restaurant and a real gem in Washington DC. Love the service and food is to die for. Try their sardines 😋😋

Staff was sweating and so was my table.  No A/C. 78 degrees. Waiter dripping sweat as he took our order.  I Ordered a $60 special and was served a plate of bones as it appeared that the fish was missing the filet.  Picked a little meat off the bones.   It was Very disappointing.  Another special entree was the size of my palm. Very small serving size. 4 people in my party. Three where served and the fourth waited five minutes for his.  Total cost $240 without drinks.  We had a bottle of water.  I don’t mind paying top dollar but would expect better.
Great and unique food, a nice place to sit and talk, good service

The oysters were small but very tasty.  I recommend trying.  If you are an ardent oyster lover, get 2 orders.  The beet salad was refreshing.  The rosotto lobster has a delicious flavor but the lobster was s little rubbery.  I did not like the texture.  The service was impeccable.  The rose wine is a must try if you like rose wine.  The desserts are excellent.  The blackberry sorbet is a winner.  My experience was wonderful and I’m planning to go back soon.
Great feast selection great choices for food the food is very fresh and delicious would I recommend that
Top quality food presented beautifully

Really great meal along with good service.  My wife and I started with grilled sardines which were well prepared.   I then had the whole branzino which was stuffed with some rosemary and other herbs.   Great to get a good fish meal also with some choices that are a bit more unusual compared to most restaurants
Not as goodcaa in the past
Good food& service!!!
Enjoyed it all
Everything we had was delicious. Service is nice.
The customer service was awesome will definitely return. I had a season item of oxtails and scallops beautifully made.

Divine lobster bisque, absolutely to die for. The main lobster dish unfortunately paled in comparison, was bland. But, substantial. Very lovely service, a great wine list, and good advice on wine selection.

Chef Andrew has created a one-in-a-gazillion seafood inspired dining establishments. The dining experience is flawless and wonderfully personalized. The food is FRESH and delicious. We enjoy a 3-course lobster special which was amazing 😉. The lobster bisque, lobster salad with roasted beets, goat cheese & arugula, and lobster with olive oil, butter & garlic was so deliciously memorable. The staff seem to vibe well with each and their rhythm is seamless. Put Pesce on your regular Go-To list.
Great service, very fresh ingredients. Everything was cooked to perfection.
Nice all fishes restaurant with fresh menu changing every day depending of the market.
Fresh, creative menu. Excellent service.
Visited a year ago and am still raving about the seafood. #Sofresh #delicious
Excellent seafood. Flavor forward. Great, friendly staff, including owner/chef who may personally check on you.

For those of us who appreciate truly exceptional seafood, we are fortunate to have Pesce in Washington, DC.  I think of the place as one of those gems of a bygone era before chain, formula and corporate eating places where kitchen help prepares dishes from photos taped to the wall. What you order at Pesce is individually prepared by the owner in a small kitchen, and it is authentically exceptional.  I recently had fresh cod with artichoke that was fabulous. The only reason I give Pesce four out of five stars is that Chef/Owner LaPorta is allowing meat to creep into his seafood menu.  For example, scallops with oxtail is not my idea of how to appreciate fresh scallops.
Got to sit at the bar without reservations. So, so, so good.

The food was amazing. The appetizer portion sizes are tiny but really delicious. They also have a great selection of wine and desserts. The server was very friendly and the whole staff was just great. The 3 course lobster meal was just great!
Great food, but a bit on the overpriced end overall
Had the whole branzino. Very tastey. Very homey feel to the place. The cod special at the time wasn't as good. But overall a great experience. Service was great.

Truly mediocre and expensive.  I had dinner there last night and while the staff is very friendly - the seafood was subpar.  They have a Tuesday special with a 3 course meal of lobster.  First course was a small teacup of lobster bisque (nothing to write home about), followed by a "salad" with a few small chunks of lobster, some steamed beets, etc.  Not really a salad... and mainly looked like something you would pick out of a trash can. The end was a tiny "lobster" soaked (and I mean soaked) in butter.  Lobster looked like it was half a pound (didn't know that restaurants served lobsters that small)... and so overly seasoned that it was difficult to eat - even if there were really only 4 or 5 sizable bites to be had.  We started off the meal with some overpriced oysters (one actually made my friend a bit sick to her stomach) and an octopus app (which was the best thing we ate all night).  Again - nice staff - but we will not be returning as there are far too many superior restaurants in DC.
Main meals are tiny portions. Without an added entree you are left feeling hungry. Prices are steep, a typical one course supper with entree for two will set you back at least $100. not counting tip.

Ostensibly had all the prospects of a nice place on a Friday night. Not very many customers so service should have been great. Not so much and see that previous reviews harp about same issue. Entree was not cooked adequately and the replacement dish took forever as well as the salad. Geez. And the replacement entree was much smaller than the original and of lesser quality. Thanks. Be prepared to enter place not up to what reviews may indicate.
I was here cause some friends told this is the best fish restaurant in DC. Nice restaurant, good service the fish was good but average.

Went to this restaurant on 1 September 2018. We were staying nearby and chose this restaurant by chance. Didn't have a reservation, but we were found a table. Food was excellent. Friendly staff. Not cheap by English standards, but similar to other restaurants we visited in America.
Excellent Italian restaurant.  The owner is very nice and accommodating.

Great service and wine but food is most important in a restaurant and unfortunately it was awful.. My wife’s fish and red beet salad were just okay, nothing special but oysters and a pasta dish with king prawns were horrendous... Thanks to wine I could get rid of the taste from my mouth. 1 out of 3 prawns were okay but the other 2 had a weird metallic taste. The whole dish was laking imagination. I got only 10 pieces of pasta, which was nothing. $30-$34 for a dish that is so bad and unimaginative should be a crime.
Exquisite food, but expensive

The food was amazing! And the service was wonderful. They are sure to sustainably source their fish, which I thought was wonderful. I don't often go for seafood, but I would definitely like to visit again!

Good ambiance, good food and friendly staff.  I started with grilled sardines that were very good and I know what I say because I am Portuguese. Then I ate a tagliatelle with clams, which was also very good and with abundant number of clams. The prices are average but good quality / price. The space is very interesting and with a funny decoration.

We had the lobster menu. Had seen the sign in the window many times. Decided to research the restaurant and make reservations. Very glad we did. Lives up to its About Us. Very good food and service. A great bottle of French Chardonnay. Lobster bisque was spot on. To MN used with their version of carrot cake. Was all very satisfying.

Delicious food, but extremely small portions and very expensive for size of meal. My hisbhusand I spent $70.00 on lunch, then went next door to Subway because we were still hungry (and we are small people). Also, very sloooowwww seeserv.
Excellent seafood. Very friendly staff
Amazing food, good vibes: you more than get what you pay for. James and Andrew are awesome servers dedicated to having a great menu, knowing a lot about it, and are just straight-up cool people! :)
Awesome seafood, fresh and cooked to perfection with a creative, artful  flair... moderate pricing, most importantly wonderful people to bring it successfully together
Unique menu, attentive staff, delicious food.

Came here with my wife and her best mate. The place is rough and ready which perfectly matches the personality of the hostess. The service is similar, not very professional. We had sardines and the calamari to start which were fine. The main courses were ok but relatively small, especially the tuna dish, and certainly not value for money. We shared two deserts but they were far too sweet. Cheapest wine was around $40 a bottle. Summary, a basic venue with bad acoustics, poor service and overpriced but reasonably tasty food.
Delicious but very pricey.
remarkably mediocre - would not recommend - the food is very bland and uninteresting - neither I or the person I was with finished our fish - and we love fish - you can do better - keep looking....
Fine place

What an incredible menu. The personal attention and service were warm, friendly and welcoming. The appetizers and main courses were creative with simple ingredients which made each dish distinctly special.
Best sea good and pudding in Dupont
Very good seafood.  Seating may get crowded, but service is good.  Food is well done.  Love this place.

Fantastic. Awesome service. Attentive. Knowledgeable of the menu. Fresh food. Best little necks I have had that I personally did not rake out of the same myself. So good. Excellent food. We'll prepared. Looking forward to my next meal there.
The food was wonderful and the service was great! Love the menu, which displays how fresh everything is!
The atmosphere was boring, dated, small and temperature was hot and stuffy.
Very good restaurant for interesting seafood dishes.  Dined alone there and still had a good time.
Awesome every time I've been there
Delicious, great wine selection and good service
Absolutely love this place.  Chef Drew and staff are incredible!

So far we've been here three times. The first time was without reservations to meet friends at the bar — which quickly turned into dinner. We had such a good time we returned a few weeks later just to eat. The third time we actually brought our significant others.  Pesce is a cozy place for a meal with friends or family. They're kind of a local secret that you don't want to get out. If you love seafood this is the place for you. We had the calamari as well as the octopus to start. Fresh oysters lasted us through cocktails before friends joined us for dinner. There were rave reviews for the butter fish, linguini with clams, and the mussels. We rounded things out with an after dinner drink, an dessert with plenty of forks.  The service was very attentive and friendly (no hovering wait staff) and we felt right at home. Even though the dining room was full, we could still hold a conversation without having to raise our voices. It's one of those places where they make a point to get to know you.
Racist and yes I am Black. I came in first time. bartender n  Caucasian people acted scared to death. Ordered a Mai Tai it was awful. Told gurlfriend to meet elsewhere!!!#blacklivesmatter

Had an amazing meal ordered raw oysters , octopus  w/polenta And Bronzino .. perfectly fresh and excellent flavor service excellent and loved the atmosphere. truly enjoyable experience. would definately recommend to my friends and will definately be back ..
Sometimes the service is better than others but the food is always wonderful. They have new dishes all the time, they serve what's fresh and the atmosphere is cozy.
Tuna was of rare quantity.  A bit of ouch on the check but not sorry I went.
Lunch was quiet with fine food choices but not inexpensive.

We are visiting from New Orleans that in itself may say something. The food here is excellent no I've had the clams and linguine. The popcorn shrimp with off the chart. And I had the lobster risotto. Large succulent sweet shop in a rich White sauce. We will be back.Don and the staff is fantastic.

Delicious, well-cooked fish, served without vegetables or side dishes and with sauces of very uneven quality. Eccentric, unreliable service. We've eaten here four times, and each time was a little worse than the last. Most recently, when three out of our party of four arrived, the waiter refused to take drink orders or allow us to order appetizers, or even to look at the menu. But when our fourth arrived the waiter was all over us, lovingly describing dishes they'd sold out of while skipping over dishes actually available. A busboy broke a glass and left the shards on the floor. And then the sauce on the skate special was salty beyond belief, as if a half-bottle of soy sauce had been reduced to its saline essence. Still, if you want big slabs of expertly-cooked fish, don't care for vegetables or any other kind of side dish, don't mind scraping off inedible sauces, and are amused by weirdo staff, this is a place to consider.
My favorite fish restaurant in DC.  The branzino is great, so is the tuna and octopus.
Fresh Mediterranean seafood prepared creatively in a cozy, neighborhood setting
Mediocre . Very loud and hard to have conversation . Small portions High prices !

Disappointing. We had grilled calamari followed by scallops. The seafood itself was okay, but we were put off by details such as stale bread, rancid olive oil, and clumsy preparation of the main meal. For example, there were large, hard chunks of meat served with the scallops that overpowered rather than complemented them.
Great
(Translated by Google) I accidentally went on a business trip and had a tuna dish coming out as the main dish.  (Original) 우연찮게 출장가서 들러서 메인요리로나오는 참치 요리를 시켰고, 같이나오는 seaweed salad가 참 인상적이었습니다.
Great meal.  Went with appetizers and had a Cesar salad and very well prepared popcorn shrimp.  Light and very fresh.  Time for a run.

I have been coming to Pesce for many years and have always received consistently great seafood and service. The owner is charming; the beautiful hostess pays attention to everyone that walks in. highly recommend it!
Delicious! !!!

I usually take my guests here. But this time, the service was terrible. I had a delegate visiting from out of town, he made the terrible mistake of asking for "garlic bread", to which he got a lecture that this is not that kind of restaurant and that they don't serve american or chinese for people who crave it.  The waiters made several mistakes throughout the evenings, such as filling with my friend's bottle, and then dumping the drink when I told them they made a mistake and I wasnt drinking what he was drinking.  We went at a non-busy time on Monday. At 7:00 pm. This was my worst experience. It is a shame because the food was good, but I wasn't there just for the food. They ruined my experience.

I don't know how they got a 26 from Zagat, it was quite disappointing. More than the money I spent is the fact that I am only in DC for a few days so it means I missed out on having a great dinner somewhere else.  Grilled sardines were ok but any good Portuguese restaurant is as good or better.  Soft shell crab was nothing special, could have been Red Lobster.  Lobster risotto was WAY too salty and lobster was overcooked/rubbery (they took it off the bill)  Red snapper was good, quite an interesting sauce.  Definitely wouldn't go again and would not recommend it to anyone.

It's been a few years since I had the pleasure of dining at Pesce, but it is without a doubt one of the highlights of my time in DC!  I was traveling alone, staying at the Mayflower Hotel.  The concierge recommended Pesce and it was flawless!  As a single woman I am always delighted when I receive the same service (good or bad) that men or couples receive!  That is what I experienced at Pesce.  I was seated promptly with a window seat and the server came over, introduced himself gave me the specials of the evening and then left me with my glass of wine to make my decision. While there were great choices that evening, I had the best Monkfish I have ever had in my entire life!!!

I recently had a team lunch at Pesce.  The food was amazing, everyone in our party raved about the food.  The hostess and servers were top notch professionals.  Nothing bad to say about Pesce.  I plan on returning again.
A great seafood restaurant that is not overly pricey. We both had fish and it was very fresh and well garnished to give it a great taste. Well worth a visit.
Best food I have had in the city for a long time. Everything on the menu i have tried is well prepared and taste good.
cute place but food not worth the expense.
